  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Melanthius, of Rhodes, Academic philosopher, 2nd
      century B.C., Second-century BC Academic philosopher from the circle of Carneades ...who was a
      successful tragic poet before turning to philosophy. It may be that we know a tragic trimeter
      from his pen: &#x3C4;&#x1F70; &#x3B4;&#x3B5;&#x3B9;&#x3BD;&#x1F70; &#x3C0;&#x3C1;&#x3AC;&#x3C3;&#x3C3;&#x3B5;&#x3B9; &#x3C4;&#x1F70;&#x3C2; &#x3C6;&#x3C1;&#x3AD;&#x3BD;&#x3B1;&#x3C2; &#x3BC;&#x3B5;&#x3C4;&#x3BF;&#x3B9;&#x3BA;&#x3AF;&#x3C3;&#x3B1;&#x3C2; ....." Stanzel, Karl-Heinz (T&#xFC;bingen).
      "Melanthius." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth
      Schneider . Brill, 2010. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. </mads:note>
